parameters:
Mage Relm: It's a unique place. I understand why it couldn't
be used as a transportation route for the crystals.

Sister Eleo: It has a sacred atmosphere like a church. I can
understand why it has always been considered an important
place.

Thief Nora: This... the smell of blood! It smells like fresh
blood!
Clea: Goat-san is already... Let's proceed further!

Sister Eleo: Are you okay!? Sophia-san, please help with the
treatment!

The senior warrior of the Bulk Corps, Lord Goat is on the
verge of losing consciousness... The reason he didn't kill
us is his last... shred of sanity...

I want to ask as a warrior of the Bulk Corps... Please let
Lord Goat pass away as a proud warrior.
Clea: I can't do that. I came here to rescue him.
Clea: Please wait, believing in Lord Goat's return.

Do you want to proceed deeper into the Forest of
Tranquility?

Clea (I don't want to think about it, but it's probably
going to be a battle...)
Clea: Let's go, there should be a goat ahead.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: 'I never thought you would be able to
come back from that state. You really helped us a lot.'

Clea: Thanks to Goat-san's vitality, we were able to resolve
the request. We also had Eleo-san come to help.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: I remember! The sight of you
desperately taking care of us is burned into my mind!

Goat of the Bulk Gang: You're quite impressive for someone
so small, my benefactor!

Sister Eleo: It may be unnecessary to mention, but... I'm
really glad that you were saved.

Mage Relm: Getting to the main point, does the Bulk Gang
have any customs related to 'blood'?

Mage Relm: If my hypothesis is correct, the 'magic' that
turns someone into an ogre should be related to blood.

Senior warrior of the Bulk Gang: Although you are our
benefactor, let me say this: we do not rely on clever tricks
like magic in our battles!

Senior warrior of the Bulk Gang: And there are rituals
involving blood--

Goat of the Bulk Gang: The ritual of blood is a rite of
passage to become a warrior.

Mage Relm: May I see it? There might be clues to solve the
curse.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: I don't mind, come with us all the
way.
Thief Nora: Oh, you seemed angry... ugh

Cleric Sophia: For the sake of resolving this, there is no
choice but to endure it just this once.
